    "description":  "This guidance informs stakeholders about upcoming introductions to the Restricted Patient System.",
    "details":  {
                    "attachments":  [

                                    ],
                    "body":  "\u003cdiv class=\"govspeak\"\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe Mental Health Casework Section (MHCS) run online sessions on a quarterly basis. These sessions provide a greater understanding of the Secretary of State’s (SofS) functions under the Mental Health Act (MHA) 1983. This is a specialist and broad topic and the presenter will endeavour to provide you with a greater understanding of MHCS responsibilities alongside particular sections of the Act namely:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eSection 37 Hospital Orders\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eSection 41 Restriction Orders\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eSection 47/49 and 48/49 Transfers from prison\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eSection 45A and 45B Hospital directions\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe next session will be held on 18 February 2025, 10:30am to 12pm via MS Teams. If you would like to attend, \u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"https://events.teams.microsoft.com/event/0a8561f8-4e8d-4cb2-9dcf-def8e3df6162@c6874728-71e6-41fe-a9e1-2e8c36776ad8\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eplease register via this link.\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e",
